0Sam%20Weinstein%2C%20set%20out%20to%20understand%20the%20money%20behind%20the%20madness.%20Progressive%20economists%20had%20long%20understood%20that%20tech%20companies%2C%20backed%20by%20gobs%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fearly-stage-startups-turn-to-cvcs-as-vc-funding-slows-2023-6%5C%22%3Eventure%20capital%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20were%20effectively%20subsidizing%20the%20price%20of%20their%20products%20until%20users%20couldn't%20live%20without%20them.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famazon-meta-layoffs-usher-in-era-of-revenue-per-employee-2023-3%5C%22%3EThink%20Amazon%3C%2Fa%3E%3A%20Offer%20stuff%20cheaper%20than%20anyone%20else%2C%20even%20though%20you%20lose%20money%20for%20years%2C%20until%20you%20scale%20to%20unimaginable%20proportions.%20Then%2C%20once%20you've%20crushed%20the%20competition%20and%20become%20the%20only%20game%20in%20town%2C%20you%20can%20raise%20prices%20and%20make%20your%20money%20back.%20It's%20called%20predatory%20pricing%2C%20and%20it's%20supposed%20to%20be%20illegal.%20It's%20one%20of%20the%20arguments%20that%20progressives%20in%20the%20Justice%20Department%20used%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fftc-amazon-antitrust-suit-marketplace-third-party-sellers-lawsuit-bloomberg-2023-6%5C%22%3Ebust%20up%20monopolies%3C%2Fa%3E%20like%20Standard%20Oil%20in%20the%20early%2020th%20century.%20Under%20the%20rules%20of%20capitalism%2C%20you%20aren't%20allowed%20to%20use%20your%20size%20to%20bully%20competitors%20out%20of%20the%20market.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20problem%20is%2C%20conservative%20economists%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Chicago%20have%20spent%20the%20past%2050%20years%20insisting%20that%20under%20capitalism%2C%20predatory%20pricing%20is%20not%20a%20thing.%20Their%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fheinonline.org%2FHOL%2FLandingPage%3Fhandle%3Dhein.journals%2Fantlervi4%26div%3D38%26id%3D%26page%3D%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehead-spinning%20argument%3C%2Fa%3E%20goes%20like%20this%3A%20Predators%20have%20a%20larger%20market%20share%20to%20begin%20with%2C%20so%20if%20they%20cut%20prices%2C%20they%20stand%20to%20lose%20much%20more%20money%20than%20their%20competitors.%20Meanwhile%20their%20prey%20can%20simply%20flee%20the%20market%20and%20return%20later%2C%20like%20protomammals%20sneaking%20back%20to%20the%20jungle%20after%20the%20velociraptors%20leave.%20Predatory%20companies%20could%20never%20recoup%20their%20losses%2C%20which%20meant%20predatory%20behaviors%20are%20%3Cem%3Eirrational%3C%2Fem%3E.%20And%20since%20Chicago%20School%20economists%20are%20the%20kind%20of%20economists%20who%20believe%20that%20markets%20are%20always%20rational%2C%20that%20means%20predatory%20pricing%20cannot%2C%20by%20definition%2C%20exist.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Supreme%20Court%20bought%20the%20argument.%20In%20the%201986%20case%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsupreme.justia.com%2Fcases%2Ffederal%2Fus%2F475%2F574%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMatsushita%20Electric%20Industry%20Co.%20v.%20Zenith%20Radio%20Corp%3Cem%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20court%20famously%20ruled%20that%20%26quot%3Bpredatory%20pricing%20schemes%20are%20rarely%20tried%2C%20and%20even%20more%20rarely%20successful.%26quot%3B%20And%20in%201993%2C%20in%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsupreme.justia.com%2Fcases%2Ffederal%2Fus%2F509%2F209%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBrooke%20Group%20v.%20Brown%20%26amp%3B%20Williamson%20Tobacco%20Corp.%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20court%20said%20that%20to%20convict%20a%20company%20of%20predatory%20pricing%2C%20prosecutors%20had%20to%20show%20not%20only%20that%20the%20accused%20predators%20had%20cut%20prices%20below%20market%20rates%20but%20also%20that%20they%20had%20a%20%26quot%3Bdangerous%20probability%26quot%3B%20of%20recouping%20their%20losses.%20That%20effectively%20shut%20down%20the%20government's%20ability%20to%20prosecute%20companies%20for%20predatory%20pricing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20last%20time%20I%20checked%2C%20no%20one%20%E2%80%94%20including%20the%20United%20States%20government%20%E2%80%94%20has%20won%20a%20predatory%20pricing%20case%20since%20Brooke%20Group%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Spencer%20Waller%2C%20an%20antitrust%20expert%20at%20Loyola's%20School%20of%20Law.%20%26quot%3BEither%20they%20can't%20prove%20below-cost%20pricing%2C%20or%20they%20can't%20prove%20recoupment%2C%20because%20a%20nonexpert%20generalist%20judge%20who%20buys%20the%20basic%20theory%20when%20they%20read%20Matsushita%20and%20Brooke%20Group%20is%20super-skeptical%20this%20stuff%20is%20ever%20rational%2C%20absent%20really%20compelling%20evidence.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELots%20of%20economists%20have%20come%20up%20with%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdoi.org%2F10.1146%2Fannurev-economics-082222-070822%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esolid%20counter-counterarguments%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20the%20Chicago%20School's%20skepticism%20about%20predatory%20pricing.%20But%20none%20of%20them%20have%20translated%20to%20winnable%20antitrust%20cases.%20Wansley%20and%20Weinstein%20%E2%80%94%20who%2C%20not%20coincidentally%2C%20used%20to%20work%20in%20antitrust%20enforcement%20at%20the%20Justice%20Department%20%E2%80%94%20set%20out%20to%20change%20that.%20In%20a%20new%20paper%20titled%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fssrn.com%2Fabstract%3D4437360%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EVenture%20Predation%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20two%20lawyers%20make%20a%20compelling%20case%20that%20the%20classic%20model%20of%20venture%20capital%20%E2%80%94%20disrupt%20incumbents%2C%20build%20a%20scalable%20platform%2C%20move%20fast%2C%20break%20things%20%E2%80%94%20isn't%20the%20peak%20of%20modern%20capitalism%20that%20Silicon%20Valley%20says%20it%20is.%20According%20to%20this%20new%20thinking%2C%20it's%20%3Cem%3Eanti%3C%2Fem%3Ecapitalist.%20It's%20illegal.%20And%20it%20should%20be%20aggressively%20prosecuted%2C%20to%20promote%20free%20and%20fair%20competition%20in%20the%20marketplace.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20think%20real%20world%20examples%20are%20not%20hard%20to%20find%20%E2%80%94%20if%20you%20look%20in%20the%20right%20place%2C%26quot%3B%20Wansley%20and%20Weinstein%20write.%20%26quot%3BA%20new%20breed%20of%20predator%20is%20emerging%20in%20Silicon%20Valley.%26quot%3B%20And%20the%20mechanism%20those%20predators%20are%20using%20to%20illegally%20dominate%20the%20market%20is%20venture%20capital%20itself.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EVenture%20investing%20is%20the%20answer%20to%20the%20question%20of%20what%20would%20happen%20if%20you%20staffed%20a%20bank's%20loan%20department%20with%20adrenaline%20junkies.%20The%20limited%20partners%20in%20venture%20funds%20demand%20high%20returns%2C%20and%20those%20funds%20are%20transient%20things%2C%20lasting%20maybe%20a%20decade%2C%20which%20means%20the%20clock%20is%20ticking.%20Venture%20capitalists%20and%20the%20investors%20who%20put%20money%20into%20their%20funds%20aren't%20necessarily%20looking%20for%20a%20successful%20product%20(though%20they%20wouldn't%20turn%20one%20down).%20For%20VCs%20and%20their%20limited%20partners%2C%20the%20most%20profitable%20endgame%20is%20a%20quick%20exit%20%E2%80%94%20either%20selling%20off%20the%20company%20or%20taking%20it%20public%20in%20an%20IPO.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThose%20pressures%2C%20Wansley%20and%20Weinstein%20argue%2C%20encourage%20risky%20strategies%20%E2%80%94%20including%20predatory%20pricing.%20%26quot%3BIf%20you%20buy%20what%20the%20Chicago%20School%20of%20economists%20think%20about%20self-funded%20predators%2C%20you%20might%20think%20it's%20irrational%20for%20a%20company%20to%20engage%20in%20predatory%20pricing%20for%20a%20bunch%20of%20reasons%2C%26quot%3B%20Weinstein%20says.%20%26quot%3BBut%20it%20might%20not%20be%20irrational%20for%20a%20VC.%26quot%3B%20The%20idea%20that%20it's%20so%20irrational%20as%20to%20be%20nonexistent%20is%20%26quot%3Ba%20bullshit%20line%20that%20has%20somehow%20become%20common%20wisdom.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETake%20Uber%2C%20one%20of%20their%20key%20examples.%20It'd%20be%20one%20thing%20if%20the%20company%20had%20simply%20outcompeted%20taxicabs%20on%20the%20merits.%20Cabs%2C%20after%20all%2C%20were%20themselves%20a%20fat%20and%20complacent%20monopoly.%20%26quot%3BMatt%20and%20I%20don't%20have%20any%20problem%20with%20that%2C%26quot%3B%20Weinstein%20says.%20%26quot%3BYou%20have%20a%20new%20product%2C%20scale%20quickly%2C%20and%20use%20some%20subsidies%20to%20get%20people%20on%20board.%26quot%3B%20Disrupt%20an%20old%20business%20and%20make%20a%20new%20one.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20that's%20not%20what%20happened.%20As%20in%20a%20soap%20opera%20or%20a%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wired.com%2Fstory%2Fwandavision-marvel-dc-star-wars-multiverse-collapse%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecomic-book%20multiverse%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20ending%20never%20arrived.%20Uber%20kept%20subsidizing%20riders%20and%20drivers%2C%20losing%20billions%20trying%20to%20spend%20its%20competitors%20into%20oblivion.%20The%20same%20goes%20for%20a%20lot%20of%20other%20VC-backed%20companies.%20%26quot%3BWeWork%20was%20setting%20up%20offices%20right%20next%20to%20other%20coworking%20spaces%20and%20saying%2C%20'We'll%20give%20you%2012%20months%20free.'%20Bird%20was%20scattering%20its%20scooters%20all%20over%20cities%2C%26quot%3B%20Wansley%20says.%20%26quot%3BThe%20pattern%20to%20us%20just%20seems%20very%20familiar.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cblockquote%3E%3Cq%3EUber%20is%20one%20of%20the%20best%20investments%20in%20history%2C%20and%20it%20was%20a%20predatory%20pricing.%3C%2Fq%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20its%20face%2C%20it%20also%20seems%20to%20prove%20the%20point%20of%20the%20Chicago%20School%3A%20that%20companies%20can%20never%20recoup%20the%20losses%20they%20incur%20through%20predatory%20pricing.%20Matsushita%20and%20Brooke%20Group%20require%20that%20prosecutors%20show%20harm.%20But%20if%20the%20only%20outcome%20of%20the%20scaling%20strategy%20used%20by%20Uber%20and%20other%20VC%20startups%20is%20to%20create%20an%20endless%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2021%2F06%2F08%2Ftechnology%2Ffarewell-millennial-lifestyle-subsidy.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emillennial%20lifestyle%20subsidy%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%26quot%3B%20that%20just%20means%20wealth%20is%20being%20transferred%20from%20investors%20to%20consumers.%20The%20only%20victims%20of%20predatory%20pricing%20are%20the%20predators%20themselves.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhere%20Wansley%20and%20Weinstein%20break%20important%20new%20ground%20is%20on%20the%20other%20legal%20standard%20set%20by%20the%20Supreme%20Court%3A%20recoupment%20of%20losses.%20If%20Uber%20and%20WeWork%20and%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20unicorns%20are%20perpetual%20money%20losers%2C%20it%20sounds%20like%20the%20standard%20isn't%20met.%20But%20Wansley%20and%20Weinstein%20point%20out%20that%20it%20can%20be%20%E2%80%94%20even%20if%20the%20companies%20never%20earn%20a%20dime%20and%20even%20if%20everyone%20who%20invests%20in%20the%20companies%2C%20post-IPO%2C%20loses%20their%20bets.%20That's%20because%20the%20venture%20capitalists%20who%20seeded%20the%20company%20%3Cem%3Edo%3C%2Fem%3E%20profit%20from%20the%20predatory%20pricing.%20They%20get%20in%2C%20get%20a%20hefty%20return%20on%20their%20investment%2C%20and%20get%20out%20before%20the%20whole%20scheme%20collapses.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWill%20Uber%20ever%20recoup%20the%20losses%20from%20its%20sustained%20predation%3F%26quot%3B%20Wansley%20and%20Weinstein%20write.%20%26quot%3BWe%20do%20not%20know.%20Our%20point%20is%20that%2C%20%3Cem%3Efrom%20the%20perspective%20of%20the%20VCs%20who%20funded%20the%20predation%2C%20it%20does%20not%20matter%3C%2Fem%3E.%20All%20that%20matters%20is%20that%20investors%20were%20willing%20to%20buy%20the%20VCs'%20shares%20at%20a%20high%20price.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELet's%20be%20clear%20here%3A%20This%20isn't%20the%20traditional%20capitalist%20story%20of%20%26quot%3Byou%20win%20some%2C%20you%20lose%20some.%26quot%3B%20The%20point%20isn't%20that%20venture%20capitalists%20sometimes%20invest%20in%20companies%20that%20don't%20make%20their%20money%20back.%20The%20point%20is%20that%20the%20entire%20model%20deployed%20by%20VCs%20is%20to%20profit%20by%20disrupting%20the%20marketplace%20with%20predatory%20pricing%2C%20and%20leave%20the%20losses%20to%20the%20suckers%20who%20buy%20into%20the%20IPO.%20A%20company%20that%20engages%20in%20predatory%20pricing%20and%20its%20late-stage%20investors%20might%20not%20recoup%2C%20but%20the%20venture%20investors%20do.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20single%20most%20important%20fact%20in%20this%20paper%20is%20that%20Benchmark%20put%20%2412%20million%20into%20Uber%20and%20got%20%245.8%20billion%20back%2C%26quot%3B%20Wansley%20says.%20%26quot%3BThat's%20one%20of%20the%20best%20investments%20in%20history%2C%20and%20it%20was%20a%20predatory%20pricing.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20new%20insight%20%E2%80%94%20that%20venture%20capital%20is%20predatory%20pricing%20in%20a%20new%20wrapper%20%E2%80%94%20could%20prove%20transformative.%20By%20translating%20the%20Silicon%20Valley%20jargon%20of%20exits%20and%20scaling%20into%20the%20legalese%20of%20antitrust%20law%2C%20Wansley%20and%20Weinstein%20have%20opened%20a%20door%20for%20the%20prosecution%20of%20tech%20investors%20and%20their%20anticompetitive%20behavior.%20%26quot%3BCourts%20will%20have%20to%20adjust%20the%20way%20they're%20thinking%20about%20recoupment%2C%26quot%3B%20Weinstein%20says.%20%26quot%3BWhat%20did%20the%20investors%20who%20bought%20from%20the%20VCs%20think%20was%20going%20to%20happen%3F%20Did%20they%20think%20they%20were%20going%20to%20recoup%3F%26quot%3B%20That%2C%20he%20says%2C%20would%20be%20a%20%26quot%3Bpretty%20good%20pathway%26quot%3B%20for%20courts%20to%20follow%20in%20determining%20whether%20a%20company's%20practices%20are%20anticompetitive.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cblockquote%3E%3Cq%3ECapitalism%20is%20supposed%20to%20allow%20competition%20to%20foster%20innovation%20and%20choice%3B%20monopolies%20quash%20all%20that%20so%20a%20few%20people%20can%20get%20rich.%3C%2Fq%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%3Cp%3EWhat%20makes%20this%20argument%20particularly%20powerful%2C%20from%20a%20legal%20perspective%2C%20is%20that%20it%20doesn't%20reject%20the%20basics%20of%20the%20Chicago%20School's%20thinking%20on%20antitrust.%20It%20accepts%20that%20consumer%20welfare%20and%20the%20efficiency%20of%20markets%20are%20paramount.%20It%20just%20points%20out%20that%20something%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fspectrum.ieee.org%2Fthe-uncanny-valley%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Euncanny%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20and%20illegal%20%E2%80%94%20is%20taking%20place%20in%20Silicon%20Valley.%20%26quot%3BI'm%20pro-enforcement%20and%20anti-Chicago%20School%2C%20so%20I'm%20always%20looking%20for%20areas%20where%20I%20think%20they're%20wrong%2C%26quot%3B%20Weinstein%20says.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20here's%20one.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20kind%20of%20%26quot%3Bserious%20legal%20scholarship%26quot%3B%20can%20be%20particularly%20successful%20with%20the%20courts%2C%20according%20to%20Waller%2C%20the%20antitrust%20expert%20at%20Loyola.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20a%20good%2C%20modest%20strategy%20to%20say%2C%20'We%20think%20your%20model's%20wrong%2C%20but%20even%20if%20your%20model's%20right%20in%20general%2C%20it's%20not%20right%20here.'%20That's%20both%20how%20you%20win%20cases%20and%20how%20you%20chip%20away%20at%20an%20edifice%20you%20want%20to%20challenge.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20so%20many%20industries%20imploding%20into%20oligopolies%20%E2%80%94%20tech%2C%20healthcare%2C%20pharma%2C%20entertainment%2C%20journalism%2C%20retail%20%E2%80%94%20it's%20a%20hopeful%20sign%20to%20see%20the%20trustbusting%20mindset%20stirring%20to%20life%20once%20more.%20Capitalism%20is%20supposed%20to%20allow%20competition%20to%20foster%20innovation%20and%20choice%3B%20monopolies%20quash%20all%20that%20so%20a%20few%20people%20can%20get%20rich.%20But%20the%20new%20scholarship%20on%20predatory%20pricing%20could%20ripple%20well%20beyond%20the%20courts.%20Wansley%20and%20Weinstein's%20paper%20put%20me%20in%20mind%20of%20%26quot%3BThe%20Big%20Con%2C%26quot%3B%20David%20Maurer's%20linguistic%20study%20of%20con%20artists%20first%20published%20in%201940.%20Maurer%20said%20the%20most%20delicate%20part%20of%20a%20con%20was%20the%20end%20%E2%80%94%20the%20%3Cem%3Eblow-off%3C%2Fem%3E.%20After%20the%20sucker%20has%20been%20bled%20dry%2C%20the%20grifter%20has%20to%20ditch%20the%20victim%2C%20ideally%20in%20such%20a%20way%20that%20they%20won't%20go%20to%20the%20cops.%20In%20the%20perfect%20crime%2C%20the%20mark%20doesn't%20even%20know%20they've%20been%20had.%20The%20transfer%20of%20lousy%20tech%20equity%20to%20late-stage%20investors%20who%20have%20been%20led%20to%20believe%20it's%20valuable%20sure%20looks%20like%20a%20good%20blow-off%20to%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20now%20that%20we%20know%20precisely%20how%20Silicon%20Valley's%20big%20con%20works%2C%20maybe%20the%20marks%20won't%20be%20so%20quick%20to%20fall%20for%20it.%20Once%20you%20know%20what%20a%20phishing%20email%20looks%20like%2C%20you%20tend%20to%20stop%20replying%20to%20them.%20The%20same%20goes%20for%20recognizing%20the%20outlines%20of%20this%20particular%20grift.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20not%20a%20Ponzi%20scheme%2C%20but%20it%20favors%20certain%20investors%2C%26quot%3B%20Weinstein%20says.%20%26quot%3BIf%20people%20in%20Silicon%20Valley%20start%20thinking%20about%20this%20as%20a%20predatory%20pricing%20scam%2C%20then%20I%20think%20the%20late-stage%20investors%20will%20start%20asking%20questions.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20not%20just%20about%20ride%20hailing%20or%20office%20sharing.%20Maybe%20grocery%20delivery%3F%20Or%20streaming-service%20subscriptions%3F%20The%20same%20kind%20of%20%3Cem%3Eaha!%20%3C%2Fem%3Elight%20that%20went%20off%20for%20Wansley%20during%20his%20interview%20with%20the%20Lyft%20executive%20could%20start%20to%20go%20off%20for%20other%20people%20as%20well.%20Some%20of%20them%20will%20be%20investors%20who%20decide%20not%20to%20park%20their%20money%20in%20predatory%20tech%20companies.%20And%20some%20of%20them%2C%20perhaps%2C%20will%20be%20government%20regulators%20who%20are%20looking%20for%20ways%20to%20bust%20our%20modern-day%20trusts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Fadam-rogers%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EAdam%20Rogers%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Cem%3Eis%20a%20senior%20correspondent%20at%20Insider.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fventure-capital-big-tech-antitrust-predatory-pricing-uber-wework-bird-2023-7%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1689673980000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64a333764cc8540019cb4f9f%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fventure-capital-big-tech-antitrust-predatory-pricing-uber-wework-bird-2023-7%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22New%20research%20reveals%20that%20Silicon%20Valley%20uses%20predatory%20pricing%20to%20crush%20competitors%20and%20scam%20investors%20%E2%80%94%20evidence%20the%20government%20can%20use%20to%20bust%20up%20tech%20monopolies.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22arogers%40insider.com%20(Adam%20Rogers)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A1%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fventure-capital-big-tech-antitrust-predatory-pricing-uber-wework-bird-2023-7%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22NDA's%2038%20vs%20oppn's%2026%3A%20List%20of%20parties%20attending%20rival%20meetings%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1689673900000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-101857303%2Cimgsize-79946.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Findia%2Fndas-38-vs-oppositions-26-list-of-parties-attending-mega-political-meetings-in-delhi-bengaluru%2Farticleshow%2F101856827.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22TIMESOFINDIA.COM%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A12%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Findia%2Fndas-38-vs-oppositions-26-list-of-parties-attending-mega-political-meetings-in-delhi-bengaluru%2Farticleshow%2F101856827.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Trapped%20in%20a%20%E2%80%98Reproductive%20Economy%E2%80%99%2C%20Most%20Women%20Can%E2%80%99t%20Access%20Property%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F03%2F25151359%2FIMG_3857.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%E2%80%9CWhen%20the%20husband%20and%20wife%20are%20treated%20as%20two%20wheels%20of%20a%20family%20cart%2C%20then%20the%20contribution%20made%20either%20by%20the%20husband%20by%20earning%20or%20the%20wife%20by%20serving%20and%20looking%20after%20the%20family%20and%20children%2C%20would%20be%20for%20the%20welfare%20of%20the%20family%20and%20both%20are%20entitled%20equally%20to%20whatever%20they%20earned%20by%20their%20joint%20effort.%20The%20proper%20presumption%20is%20that%20the%20beneficial%20interest%20belongs%20to%20them%20jointly.%20The%20property%20may%20be%20purchased%20either%20in%20the%20name%20of%20husband%20or%20wife%20alone%2C%20but%20nevertheless%2C%20it%20is%20purchased%20with%20the%20monies%20saved%20by%20their%20joint%20efforts.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20recent%20landmark%20judgement%20by%20the%20Madras%20high%20court%20%3Cem%3E(Kannaian%20Naidu%20vs%20Kamsala%20Ammal)%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0shines%20a%20spotlight%20on%20three%20interrelated%20issues.%20First%2C%20the%20gendered%20roles%20and%20responsibilities%20dictated%20by%20social%20norms%2C%20the%20structural%20inequality%20faced%20by%20women%20in%20our%20country%2C%20and%20the%20interplay%20of%20norms%20and%20lack%20of%20legislations%20for%20gender%20equality%20in%20an%20intimate%20relationship%20can%20have%20material%20(and%20non-material)%20consequences%20for%20the%20parties%20involved.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20short%2C%20the%20Madras%20high%20court%20held%20that%20a%20wife%20as%20a%20homemaker%20is%20entitled%20to%20an%20equal%20share%20in%20marital%20property%20as%20she%20has%20performed%20household%20chores%20round%20the%20clock%2C%20thereby%20enabling%20the%20husband%20to%20engage%20in%20gainful%20employment%20and%20accumulate%20sufficient%20savings%20to%20purchase%20property.%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack.com%2Fredirect%2F37c1e0ee-614f-4025-9b0c-fca3aedfcf73%3Fj%3DeyJ1IjoiYWt5Mm8ifQ.6MWfvlP9rau_ovHEjX2OsfccTssIZEXNjPP_vKEvs5I%5C%22%20data-saferedirecturl%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.google.com%2Furl%3Fq%3Dhttps%3A%2F%2Fsubstack.com%2Fredirect%2F37c1e0ee-614f-4025-9b0c-fca3aedfcf73%3Fj%253DeyJ1IjoiYWt5Mm8ifQ.6MWfvlP9rau_ovHEjX2OsfccTssIZEXNjPP_vKEvs5I%26amp%3Bsource%3Dgmail%26amp%3Bust%3D1689733716250000%26amp%3Busg%3DAOvVaw1j61pY2B9PkOeIOhXjbmF8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20judgment%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20its%20entirety%20is%20well%20worth%20reading%2C%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack.com%2Fredirect%2F0e735cb7-a956-4065-8898-3335b03499ab%3Fj%3DeyJ1IjoiYWt5Mm8ifQ.6MWfvlP9rau_ovHEjX2OsfccTssIZEXNjPP_vKEvs5I%5C%22%20data-saferedirecturl%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.google.com%2Furl%3Fq%3Dhttps%3A%2F%2Fsubstack.com%2Fredirect%2F0e735cb7-a956-4065-8898-3335b03499ab%3Fj%253DeyJ1IjoiYWt5Mm8ifQ.6MWfvlP9rau_ovHEjX2OsfccTssIZEXNjPP_vKEvs5I%26amp%3Bsource%3Dgmail%26amp%3Bust%3D1689733716250000%26amp%3Busg%3DAOvVaw1e7n4yZ5Rqbohifilq-Nws%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eand%20a%20shorter%20summary%20is%20here%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20most%20societies%20around%20the%20world%2C%20including%20in%20India%2C%20the%20male%20breadwinner%20and%20female%20caregiver%20model%20is%20deeply%20entrenched.%20This%20social%20expectation%20affects%20women%20and%20girls%20from%20the%20cradle%20to%20the%20grave.%20Admittedly%2C%20men%20suffer%20too%2C%20but%20in%20a%20patriarchal%20society%2C%20women%20are%20much%20worse%20off.%20From%20an%20early%20age%2C%20girls%20are%20socialised%20to%20perform%20well%20in%20the%20reproductive%20economy%20encompassing%20biological%20reproduction%20and%20social%20reproduction%2C%20including%20home%20maintenance%2C%20child%20rearing%2C%20elderly%20care%20and%20transmission%20of%20cultural%20values.%20Men%2C%20on%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20are%20expected%20to%20participate%20in%20the%20productive%20economy%20and%20put%20bread%20on%20the%20table%20for%20their%20spouses%2C%20children%20and%20parents.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20gendered%20social%20contract%20translates%20into%20structural%20inequalities%20that%20largely%20impact%20women%20far%20more%20negatively%20than%20they%20do%20men.%20Fewer%20resources%20are%20invested%20in%20girls%20in%20terms%20of%20education%20and%20health.%20Investment%20in%20women%20is%20not%20approached%20through%20a%20lens%20of%20social%20and%20economic%20equality%2C%20but%20from%20the%20perspective%20of%20families%20and%20communities%20which%20will%20thrive%20with%20healthy%20and%20educated%20women%20in%20their%20midst.%20Given%20women%E2%80%99s%20reproductive%20responsibilities%2C%20their%20participation%20in%20the%20productive%20economy%20remains%20low.%20Women%E2%80%99s%20labour%20and%20contribution%20to%20the%20reproductive%20economy%20remains%20invisible%2C%20taken%20for%20granted%2C%20and%20euphemistically%20termed%20%E2%80%98priceless%E2%80%99%20when%20any%20attempt%20is%20made%20to%20value%20this%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20judgement%20correctly%20points%20out%20that%20women%E2%80%99s%20reproductive%20labour%20%E2%80%9Cfrees%20her%20husband%20for%20his%20economic%20activities%E2%80%9D.%20Thus%2C%20as%20a%20matter%20of%20economic%20justice%2C%20both%20spouses%20should%20be%20the%20legal%20owners%20of%20property%20and%20other%20assets%20acquired%20during%20marriage.%20This%20can%20be%20achieved%20by%20a%20gender%20egalitarian%20marital%20regime%20(rules%20governing%20the%20ownership%20and%20management%20of%20property%20during%20marriage%20and%20upon%20its%20dissolution).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBroadly%2C%20there%20are%20community%20property%20and%20separation%20of%20property%20regimes.%20In%20community%20property%2C%20all%20assets%20acquired%20during%20marriage%20are%20treated%20as%20belonging%20to%20both%20spouses.%20Assets%20acquired%20prior%20to%20marriage%20or%20inheritances%20received%20is%20considered%20individually%20owned%20in%20partial%20community%2C%20whereas%20in%20full%20community%2C%20such%20assets%20are%20also%20jointly%20owned.%20In%20contrast%2C%20the%20separation%20of%20property%20marital%20regime%20treats%20all%20property%20irrespective%20of%20the%20time%20of%20acquisition%2C%20as%20individually%20owned%20property.%20Thus%2C%20community%20of%20property%20recognises%20women%E2%80%99s%20contribution%20to%20marital%20assets%20via%20their%20reproductive%20labour.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECommunity%20of%20property%20is%20of%20great%20relevance%20in%20a%20country%20like%20India%2C%20where%20women%E2%80%99s%20avenues%20for%20asset%20acquisition%20are%20limited.%20Women%20do%20not%20typically%20inherit%20from%20their%20parents%20and%20due%20to%20their%20low%20labour%20force%20participation%2C%20often%20lack%20sufficient%20earnings%20to%20purchase%20property%20and%20other%20high-value%20assets.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAn%20analysis%20by%20Deere%C2%A0%3Cem%3Eet%20al%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0(2013)%20across%20different%20marital%20regimes%20found%20that%20separation%20of%20property%20regime%20is%20disadvantageous%20to%20married%20women%20(Ghana%20and%20Karnataka)%20compared%20to%20partial%20community%20property%20(Ecuador).%20This%20is%20confirmed%20with%20recent%20data%20from%20the%20All%20India%20Debt%20and%20Investment%20Survey%20(2019)%20which%20for%20the%20first-time%20included%20information%20on%20ownership%20of%20land%20by%20individuals%20within%20a%20household.%20Unfortunately%2C%20an%20individual%E2%80%99s%20marital%20status%20is%20not%20collected.%20Our%20analysis%20shows%20that%20only%207%25%20of%20married%20women%20own%20land%20in%20landed%20households.%20The%20comparable%20number%20is%2093%25%20for%20currently%20single%20women.%20Presumably%2C%20the%20currently%20single%20category%20is%20largely%20comprised%20of%20widows%20who%20inherit%20their%20husband%E2%80%99s%20property.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndian%20society%20should%20not%20have%20to%20wait%20for%20enlightened%20judgements%20to%20realise%20the%20goal%20of%20gender%20equality%20that%20is%20promised%20under%20our%20Constitution.%20We%20urgently%20need%20laws%20to%20deliver%20on%20this%20promise%20so%20that%20all%20married%20women%20have%20rights%20and%20entitlements%20within%20marriage%20without%20having%20to%20approach%20the%20court%20for%20redress.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EHema%20Swaminathan%20and%20Supriya%20Lakhtakia%20are%20at%20IIM%20Bangalore%2C%20Rahul%20Lahoti%20is%20at%20the%20UN%20University.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20piece%20was%20first%20published%20on%20The%20India%20Cable%20%E2%80%93%20a%20premium%20newsletter%20from%20The%20Wire%20%26amp%3B%20Galileo%20Ideas%20%E2%80%93%20and%20has%20been%20republished%20here.%20To%20subscribe%20to%20The%20India%20Cable%2C%20click%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Ftheindiacable.com%2F%5C%22%3Ehere%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1689673879000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F03%2F25151359%2FIMG_3857.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fwomen%2Fwomen-family-property-inheritence%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Analysis%20shows%20that%20only%207%25%20of%20married%20women%20own%20land%20in%20landed%20households.%20The%20comparable%20number%20is%2093%25%20for%20currently%20single%20women.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fwomen%2Fwomen-family-property-inheritence%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22In%20Pics%3A%20Hugs%20And%20Handshakes%20As%20Opposition%20Leaders%20Meet%20In%20Bengaluru%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3ELeaders%20from%2026%20opposition%20parties%20gathered%20in%20Bengaluru%20today%20to%20present%20a%20united%20front%20to%20take%20on%20the%20PM%20Narendra%20Modi-led%20NDA%20in%20the%202024%20Lok%20Sabha%20polls.%20The%20formal%20talks%20will%20take%20place%20today%20from%2011%20am%20to%204%20pm.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20opposition%20leaders%20were%20seen%20shaking%20hands%20and%20sharing%20hugs%20as%20they%20greeted%20each%20other%20ahead%20of%20the%20closed-door%20meeting%20in%20Bengaluru.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%2239je5f8o%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-07%2F39je5f8o_opposition-meet_625x300_18_July_23.jpg%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETamil%20Nadu%20Chief%20Minister%20and%20DMK%20leader%20presents%20a%20book%20to%20Congress's%20Sonia%20Gandhi%20as%20Trinamool%20Congress%20chief%20Mamata%20Banerjee%20and%20DK%20Shivakumar%20look%20on.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22phj2dlbo%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-07%2Fphj2dlbo_opposition-meet_625x300_18_July_23.jpg%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERJD%20president%20Lalu%20Prasad%20Yadav%20shares%20a%20light%20moment%20with%20Rahul%20Gandhi%2C%20Sonia%20Gandhi%2C%20D%20Raja%2C%20Tejashwi%20Yadav%20And%20Mamata%20Banerjee.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22pvim933g%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-07%2Fpvim933g_opposition-meet_625x300_18_July_23.jpeg%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECongress%20Leader%20Rahul%20Gandhi%