ke-up-early-2019-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eget%20up%20early%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20get%20to%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20bought%20into%20the%20idea%20that%20I%20was%20and%20would%20always%20be%20a%20failure%20if%20I%20couldn't%20master%20my%20biorhythm%20and%20become%20a%20super-productive%20early%20bird.%20But%20it%20just%20doesn't%20work%20for%20me%20and%20my%20routine.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EFor%20a%20while%20I%20set%20an%20early%20alarm%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20dragged%20myself%20out%20of%20bed%20between%205%20and%206%20a.m.%20and%20tried%20to%20get%20my%20morning%20started%20with%20coffee%20from%20my%20French%20press.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESometimes%20it%20would%20work%2C%20but%20more%20often%20than%20not%20I'd%20find%20myself%20procrastinating%20getting%20to%20the%20computer%20once%20I%20was%20awake%20%E2%80%94%20or%20if%20I%20did%20get%20there%2C%20I'd%20make%20minimal%20progress%20on%20any%20work%20for%20a%20long%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20felt%20awful%20that%20it%20was%20so%20hard%20for%20me.%20I%20thought%20I%20really%20shouldn't%20be%20the%20CEO%20of%20a%20business%20if%20I%20couldn't%20get%20up%20early.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20also%20frustrating%20that%20no%20matter%20how%20tired%20I%20felt%20in%20the%20morning%20and%20again%20in%20the%20afternoon%2C%20I'd%20get%20a%20second%20wind%20at%208%20p.m.%20I'd%20feel%20energized%20and%20creative%20and%20could%20work%20or%20hang%20out%20late.%20Knowing%20this%20would%20sabotage%20my%20morning%2C%20I'd%20fight%20the%20wave%20of%20energetic%20flow%20to%20try%20to%20get%20to%20bed%20early%20to%20start%20the%20cycle%20again.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ETrying%20to%20fit%20into%20someone%20else's%20productivity%20hack%20made%20me%20grumpy%2C%20angry%2C%20and%20frustrated%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20two%20or%20three%20years%20of%20trying%20and%20failing%20to%20be%20a%20morning%20person%2C%20I%20realized%20that%20the%20only%20way%20to%20be%20successful%20was%20to%20do%20it%20my%20way