%3C%2Fem%3EPawar%20said%20that%20the%20second-rung%20leadership%20that%20joined%20the%20Bharatiya%20Janata%20Party%20(BJP)%20was%20pressurising%20him%20to%20agree%20to%20joining%20the%20saffron%20party.%20And%20it%20was%20going%20for%20a%20long%20time%2C%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CHowever%2C%20I%20kept%20refusing%20because%20I%20cannot%20take%20such%20a%20big%20decision%20alone%20without%20consulting%20our%20party.%20I%20take%20everyone%20into%20confidence%20before%20taking%20major%20decisions%20that%20will%20have%20long-term%20impact%20on%20party%20politics.%20I%20have%20to%20respect%20my%20cadre.%20Therefore%2C%20we%20did%20take%20a%20different%20decision%20and%20refused%20to%20go%20with%20those%20who%20aligned%20with%20the%20BJP%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20told%20the%20newspaper.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20veteran%20politician%20said%20that%20in%20a%20democracy%2C%20everybody%20is%20free%20to%20take%20a%20different%20stand%2C%20and%20added%20that%20the%20process%20to%20rebuild%20the%20party%20network%20has%20already%20started.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CAjit%20may%20have%20taken%20the%20party%20MLAs%2C%20but%20the%20cadre%20of%20the%20party%20is%20intact%20and%20remains%20with%20us.%20We%20are%20very%20much%20here%2C%20so%20we%20will%20focus%20on%20strengthening%20the%20party%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20told%20the%20daily.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20further%20said%20that%20he%20did%20not%20pay%20much%20attention%20to%20grooming%20the%20third-generation%20leadership%20in%20the%20party.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20mutiny%20showed%20the%20reality%3A%20We%20failed%20to%20fill%20a%20big%20generation%20gap%20in%20the%20party%20on%20time.%20We%20neglected%20this%20big%20space%3B%20we%20could%20have%20given%20more%20attention%20to%20it.%20The%20leadership%20potential%20and%20active%20youth%20committed%20to%20secular%20and%20progressive%20ideology%20would%20have%20filled%20this%20gap%20easily.%20However%2C%20it%20has%20also%20given%20us%20an%20opportunity%20to%20fill%