%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-101850392%2Cimgsize-127672.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fentertainment%2Fhindi%2Fbollywood%2Fnews%2Fhappy-birthday-bhumi-pednekar-5-movies-where-the-actor-proved-that-she-isnt-your-run-of-the-mill-bollywood-diva%2Fphotostory%2F101850392.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20border%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fphoto%2F101850392.cms%5C%22%20hspace%3D%5C%2210%5C%22%3EHappy%20Birthday%20Bhumi%20Pednekar%3A%205%20movies%20where%20the%20actor%20proved%20that%20she%20isn't%20your%20run-of-the-mill%20Bollywood%20diva%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A11%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fentertainment%2Fhindi%2Fbollywood%2Fnews%2Fhappy-birthday-bhumi-pednekar-5-movies-where-the-actor-proved-that-she-isnt-your-run-of-the-mill-bollywood-diva%2Fphotostory%2F101850392.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%2210%20reasons%20why%20the%20recession%20that%20Wall%20Street%20predicted%20to%20death%20never%20showed%20up%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%227007%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22This%20is%20a%20photo%20of%20a%20US%20%24100%20bill%20with%20a%20red%20arrow%20pointing%20downwards%20in%20front%20of%20it.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F62fe7288f1df7e0018eb23d7%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%225255%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20stock%20market%20could%20continue%20to%20tumble%20in%20the%20face%20of%20rising%20inflation%20and%20a%20recession.%3Cp%3Esefa%20ozel%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EFor%20months%2C%20markets%20and%20businesses%20have%20been%20bracing%20for%20a%20much-predicted%20US%20recession%20%E2%80%93%20which%20never%20showed%20up.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EAnd%20now%2C%20economists%20at%20UBS%20have%20compiled%20a%20list%20of%2010%20reasons%20why%20the%20downturn%20hasn't%20happened%20so%20far.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EGovernment%20spending%2C%20strong%20savings%2C%20and%20a%20resilient%20jobs%20market%20are%20among%20reasons%20the%20economy%20held%20up%2C%20the%20bank%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3ESince%20late%202022%2C%20a%20majority%20of%20big%20Wall%20Street%20names%20have%20repeatedly%20predicted%20a%20recession%20to%20hit%20the%20US%20economy%20this%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20more%20than%20six%20months%20into%202023%2C%20there's%20still%20no%20sign%20of%20the%20much-predicted%20output%20contraction.%20If%20anything%2C%20things%20are%20looking%20pretty%20upbeat%20%E2%80%93%20inflation%20is%20rapidly%20cooling%2C%20the%20job%20market%20is%20holding%20up%2C%20unemployment%20has%20hit%20rock%20bottom%20and%20stocks%20are%20ebullient.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20a%20deeply%20inverted%20bond%20yield%20curve%2C%20considered%20a%20classic%20warning%20sign%20for%20an%20impending%20economic%20downturn%2C%20has%20had%C2%A0little%20damping%20effect%20on%20investor%20sentiment%20%E2%80%93%20baffling%20many%20in%20in%20markets%20and%20businesses%20that%20have%20been%20bracing%20for%20the%20event.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEconomists%20at%20the%20Swiss%20banking%20giant%20UBS%20have%20compiled%20a%20list%20of%2010%20reasons%20why%20the%20recession%20failed%20to%20show%20up.%20Using%20the%20National%20Bureau%20of%20Economic%20Research's%20definition%20of%20the%20term%2C%20which%20tracks%20criteria%20such%20as%20consumption%2C%20production%2C%20and%20unemployment%2C%20the%20bank%20has%20produced%20a%20list%20of%20evidence%20that%20shows%20the%20US%20economy%20is%20much%20more%20resilient%20than%20many%20experts%20give%20credit%20for.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E1.%20Monetary%20policy%20isn't%20all%20that%20tight%20yet%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20after%20the%20Federal%20Reserve%20lifted%20interest%20rates%20by%20a%20staggering%20500%20basis%20points%20over%20the%20past%20five%20quarters%2C%20inflation-adjusted%20borrowing%20costs%20in%20the%20US%20still%20very%20low.%20The%20yield%20on%20the%2010-year%20Treasury%20Inflation-Indexed%20Security%20is%20currently%20just%201.52%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20central%20bank's%20balance%20sheet%2C%20which%20is%20closely%20correlated%20with%20the%20amount%20of%20money%20it%20has%20pumped%20into%20the%20economy%20via%20asset%20purchases%2C%20is%20still%2080%25%20larger%20than%20pre-pandemic%20levels%2C%20according%20to%20UBS.%20That%20suggests%20monetary%20conditions%20are%20still%20not%20tight%20by%20historical%20standards.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFinancial%20conditions%20have%20eased%20in%202023%2C%20and%20the%20Fed's%20balance%20sheet%20and%20money%20supply%20are%20very%20accommodative%20vs.%20pre-pandemic%20trends%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20Swiss%20bank%20said%20in%20a%20report.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E2.%20Government%20spending%20is%20back%20on%20the%20rise%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EGovernment%20spending%20is%20on%20the%20rise%20again%2C%20after%20a%20pullback%20last%20year%20from%20the%20largesse%20of%20the%20pandemic%20days.%20And%20that's%20also%20increasing%20the%20amount%20of%20money%20available%20in%20the%20financial%20system%2C%20cushioning%20the%20economy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Inflation%20Reduction%20Act%20of%202022%20has%20also%20helped%20stimulate%20investment%2C%20especially%20in%20the%20manufacturing%20sector%2C%20according%20to%20UBS.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E3.%20Strong%20savings%20are%20fueling%20consumption%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ESavings%20accrued%20during%20the%20pandemic%20have%20acted%20as%20a%20buffer%20against%20the%20rising%20cost%20of%20living%2C%20supporting%20consumption%20in%20the%20US%20economy.%20Additionally%2C%20financial-asset%20price%20increases%20have%20boosted%20total%20wealth.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20a%20majority%20of%20mortgages%20are%20locked%20into%20fixed%20rates%20-%20and%20that%20has%20protected%20those%20borrowers%20from%20the%20impact%20of%20the%20Fed's%20rate%20increases.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E4.%20Debt%20levels%20aren't%20too%20high%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3B%20Consumer%20debt%20levels%20and%20delinquency%20rates%20are%20in%20much%20better%20shape%20compared%20to%20pre-financial%20crisis%20in%202008%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20bank%20said%20in%20the%20note.%20%26quot%3B%20Household%20debt%20loads%20appear%20manageable.%20Credit%20card%20delinquencies%20are%20rising%2C%20but%20off%20a%20historically%20low%20base.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECompanies%20aren't%20suffering%20from%20an%20investment%20overhang%20and%20high%20inflation%20has%20deflated%20high%20debt%20levels%2C%20according%20to%20UBS.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E5.%20Credit%20conditions%20haven't%20tightened%20much%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ECredit-market%20conditions%20haven't%20turned%20unfavorable%20for%20corporate%20borrowers%2C%20even%20after%20the%20banking%20turmoil%20earlier%20this%20year%20prompted%20some%20banks%20to%20pull%20back%20on%20lending.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHigh-yield%20bond%20spreads%20are%20down%20year-to-date%2C%20according%20to%20UBS%2C%20meaning%20companies%20with%20lower%20credit%20ratings%20have%20easier%20access%20to%20public%20debt%20than%20twelve%20months%20ago.%20The%20issuance%20of%20such%20debt%20is%20on%20the%20rise%2C%20too.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E6.%20Labor%20market%20remains%20robust%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAmerican%20employers%20are%20still%20adding%20a%20sizable%20number%20of%20new%20positions%2C%20pushing%20jobless%20claims%20in%20the%20economy%20below%20pre-pandemic%20averages.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3B%20Payrolls%20are%20catching%20up%20to%20their%20pre-pandemic%20trend.%20Employment%20rates%20mostly%20near%20pre-pandemic%20levels%2C%26quot%3B%20UBS%20said%20in%20the%20note.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E7.%20Economic%20data%20trends%20are%20stabilizing%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20pandemic%20disrupted%20cyclical%20patterns%20in%20economic%20data%2C%20but%20they%20are%20returning%20back%20to%20normal%2C%20according%20to%20the%20Swiss%20bank.%20And%20that's%20likely%20signaling%20that%20the%20economy%20is%20on%20a%20more%20stable%20footing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3B%20Spending%20on%20goods%20and%20services%20is%20getting%20back%20to%20normal.%20Job%20growth%20volatility%20has%20returned%20to%20pre-pandemic%20Levels%2C%26quot%3B%20UBS%20said.%20%26quot%3B%20Supply%20bottlenecks%20are%20also%20easing%2C%20though%20not%20back%20to%20normal.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E8.%20Sectoral%20downturns%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ESeparate%20activity%20slumps%20in%20different%20parts%20of%20the%20economy%20may%20have%20helped%20prevent%20a%20full-blown%20recession%20to%20some%20extent%2C%20according%20to%20the%20bank.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBoth%20US%20manufacturing%20and%20housing%20starts%20had%20slumped%20in%202022%2C%20but%20may%20be%20recovering%20now%2C%20UBS%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E9.%20Services%20growth%20remains%20solid%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20manufacturing%20has%20seen%20some%20slowdown%2C%20its%20share%20of%20the%20economy%20is%20declining%20and%20the%20larger%20services%20sector%20has%20experienced%20sustained%20growth.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3B%20Services%20consumption%20was%20slower%20to%20recover%2C%20but%20is%20still%20growing%20and%20it's%20a%20much%20bigger%20share%20of%20the%20economy%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20bank%20said.%20%26quot%3B%20The%20manufacturing%20sector's%20share%20of%20the%20private%20sector%20continues%20to%20shrink.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E10.%20The%20economy%20is%20less%20cyclical%20now%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20economy%20has%20evolved%20structurally%20in%20a%20way%20that%20it's%20less%20vulnerable%20now%20to%20cyclical%20ups%20and%20downs%2C%20UBS%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20a%20knowledge-based%20services%20economy%20that%20has%20become%20less%20sensitive%20to%20inventory%20cycles%20and%20energy%20costs%20-%20and%20as%20a%20result%2C%20economic%20activity%20is%20less%20volatile%20and%20expansions%20can%20last%20longer%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20bank%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2F10-reasons-recession-wall-street-predicted-to-death-never-happened-2023-7%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1689668887000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F62fe7288f1df7e0018eb23d7%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fnews%2Fstocks%2F10-reasons-recession-wall-street-predicted-to-death-never-happened-2023-7%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22For%20months%2C%20markets%20and%20businesses%20have%20been%20bracing%20for%20a%20much-predicted%20US%20recession%20%E2%80%93%20but%20it%20never%20arrived.%20And%20now%2C%20economists%20at%20UBS%20have%20a%20list%20of%2010%20reasons%20why%20the%20downturn%20didn't%20happen.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22jwilkins%40insider.com%20(Joseph%20Wilkins)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A27%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fnews%2Fstocks%2F10-reasons-recession-wall-street-predicted-to-death-never-happened-2023-7%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Olympian%20named%20among%20crew%20for%20Virgin%20Galactic's%20first%20space%20tourism%20flight%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1689668760000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fe3.365dm.com%2F23%2F07%2F768x432%2Fskynews-anastatia-mayers-jon-goodwin_6221814.jpg%3F20230718095345%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Fvirgin-galactic-names-space-tourism-flight-crew-including-olympian-and-first-mother-daughter-duo-12922708%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20former%20Olympian%20has%20been%20named%20among%20the%20crew%20for%20Virgin%20Galactic's%20first%20space%20tourism%20flight.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22enga