0in%20July%2C%20which%20could%20have%20global%20consequences.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhy%20is%20the%20agreement%20important%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUkraine%20is%20one%20of%20the%20world%E2%80%99s%20largest%20grain%20suppliers.%20Ukrainian%20grain%20feeds%20400%20million%20people%20worldwide%2C%20according%20to%20World%20Food%20Program%20figures.%20When%20Russia%E2%80%99s%20full-scale%20invasion%20of%20Ukraine%20began%20in%20February%202022%2C%20many%20countries%20feared%20a%20famine.%20In%20Africa%20and%20the%20Middle%20East%20in%20particular%2C%20a%20hunger%20crisis%20threatened.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFood%20prices%20had%20already%20risen%20before%20the%20start%20of%20the%20Ukraine%20war%2C%20but%20the%20Russian%20invasion%20made%20them%20skyrocket%20worldwide.%20In%20addition%2C%20the%20Russian%20blockade%20of%20the%20Black%20Sea%20meant%20millions%20of%20tons%20of%20grain%20were%20stuck%20in%20Ukrainian%20silos%2C%20in%20danger%20of%20rotting.%20According%20to%20the%20European%20Union%20%E2%80%9Cmaintaining%20Ukrainian%20grain%20supplies%20remains%20critical%20to%20global%20food%20security.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20could%20happen%20if%20the%20deal%20expires%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIf%20Russia%20does%20not%20agree%20to%20extending%20the%20deal%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20unclear%20whether%20Ukraine%20will%20continue%20to%20ship%20the%20same%20quantities%20of%20grain%20to%20the%20world.%20The%20high%20cost%20of%20insuring%20the%20ships%20could%20be%20a%20major%20problem.%20Ships%20that%20want%20to%20cross%20the%20Black%20Sea%20already%20have%20to%20be%20insured%20for%20thousands%20of%20dollars.%20Shipping%20companies%20might%20be%20reluctant%20to%20send%20their%20ships%20through%20the%20war%20zone%20if%20there%20is%20no%20Russian%20approval.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETransporting%20grain%20overland%20could%20also%20become%20difficult.%20Since%20the%20beginning%20of%20the%20war%2C%20Ukraine%20has%20exported%20large%20quantities%20of%20grain%20via%20eastern%20EU%20countries%20%E2%80%94%20but%20there%20are%20too%20few%20freight%20carriages%20to%20export%20all%20of%20Ukraine%E2%80%99s%20grain%20over%20land.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20addition%2C%20farmers%20in%20some%20eastern%20EU%20countries%20resent%20Ukrainian%20supplies%20being%20shipped%20through%20their%20countries%2C%20saying%20it%20undercuts%20local%20supplies%20and%20effectively%20takes%20away%20markets%20for%20their%20own%20crops.%20In%20reaction%2C%20the%20European%20Union%20imposed%20import%20restrictions%20earlier%20this%20month%20that%20stipulate%20grain%20can%20be%20transported%20through%20Bulgaria%2C%20Hungary%2C%20Poland%2C%20Romania%20and%20Slovakia%20but%20cannot%20be%20sold%20in%20these%20countries.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EHow%20does%20the%20current%20deal%20work%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20agreement%20regulates%20grain%20exports%20from%20the%20Ukrainian-controlled%20Black%20Sea%20ports%20of%20Odesa%2C%20Chornomorsk%20and%20Pivdenny.%20Ships%20must%20cross%20the%20Black%20Sea%20along%20an%20agreed%20humanitarian%20sea%20corridor%20toward%20Istanbul.%20Ships%20en%20route%20to%20and%20from%20Ukrainian%20ports%20are%20checked%20at%20a%20Turkish-controlled%20base%20by%20a%20special%20team%20of%20Russian%2C%20Turkish%2C%20Ukrainian%20and%20UN%20inspectors.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETwo%20UN%20task%20forces%20ensure%20that%20Ukrainian%20grain%20can%20be%20shipped%20across%20the%20Black%20Sea%2C%20and%20they%20also%20facilitate%20the%20export%20of%20Russian%20food%20and%20fertilizer%20products.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F02%2F20165942%2F51905521463_0600c20141_k.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp